# Keep the build context minimal: ignore everything, then re-include only the
# files the image actually COPYs (the package manifests + the prebuilt dist
# bundle). Anything else in the repo — local .tmp/ worktrees, node_modules,
# .env secrets, tests, docs — is excluded by default, so the context can't
# silently bloat as the project grows.
*
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!dist
